CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 13, 1957, pg. A15 reads: "Just Married - Lewis Lee of Monessen takes first piece of wedding cake from his bride, the former Gladys Simmons, daughter of the Rev. James L. Simmons, of McKees Rocks. The Rev. A. B.  Barnes officiated at the rites.  The couple will live in Monessen. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of groom Lewis Lee and bride Gladys Simmons Lee, cutting four tiered wedding cake in interior with two toned walls and two paintings
